cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a distributed sampling problem, which involves communication and information theory aspects, making cs.IT the most likely category. The problem also involves coordination and communication between processors, which suggests categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with randomness and probability, which suggests categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
